           <note resp="Philip Lampi">The Bee (Hudson, NY) reports 359 votes for Thomas Power.</note>
           <note resp="Philip Lampi">"Two of the republican candidates for aldermen having an equal number of votes, their election will depend upon a future choice."  The Bee (Hudson, NY).  April 14, 1812.</note>
           <note resp="Philip Lampi">The Northern Whig (Hudson, NY) alleges several instances of malfeasance on the part of the Republicans in the charter elections (the city's mayor was Republican). These include the disenfranchisment of ten black men who had regularly voted in previous elections; the practice of allowing soldiers stationed in the city to vote; and the instance that some minors had been permitted to vote.</note>
